Online Gaming Safeguards and Tools

Michigan Lottery’s online services still include the industry’s most innovative and robust responsible gaming safeguards, which include:

  • Self-Exclusion – Take a break from Michigan Lottery’s online services. Your account will be closed for the selected exclusion length and will not be reopened for any reason during the exclusion period.
  • Deposit Limits – Set daily and weekly deposit limits. Change your deposit limit at any time. Lowering a deposit limit takes immediate effect, but raises to a limit are implemented after 48 hours.
  • Play History – Monitor the time and money you spend on our online games as well as your transaction history.
","account_reinstatement_page2_content":"

Tips for Betting Responsibly

Moderation is the key to responsible gaming. Some responsible gaming tips:

  • Set money and time limits for gaming and stick to them. Consider the money you spend on gaming as part of your entertainment budget and act accordingly.
  • Your gambling spending limit should be based on what you can afford to lose.
  • Avoid gaming when you’re upset, lonely, angry, depressed, or stressed.
  • Gambling is not advised for those in recovery for addictive disorders or dependencies.
","account_reinstatement_page3_content":"

Problem Gambling

Problem gambling may be treated successfully once detected. Some warning signs to help determine if you have a problem or are headed toward a problem include:

  • Missing work or sacrificing time with your family to gamble
  • Gambling is causing problems with your family
  • Lying about the time spent gambling or the money you’ve lost
  • Being unable to stop or control your betting
  • Borrowing money to gamble
  • Gambling to get money to solve financial problems
  • Selling or pawning property to get money for gambling
  • Spending money on gambling that should have gone to pay your bills
  • Gambling more to recover your losses
  • Committing a crime or considering committing a crime to pay for gambling
  • Feelings of hopelessness, depression, or suicide
","account_reinstatement_page4_content":"

Help and Support

Confidential, one-on-one support is available to any Michigan resident seeking help for a gambling problem. For assistance, including screening services and referrals to treatment or support groups, please contact any of the following local resources:

Helpline: 1-800-270-7117

Text: 248-648-3363

Live Chat: [ProblemGamblingLink|Problem Gambling]

","account_reinstatement_page5_content":"

• Box (24-way): If your 4-digit number contains 4 unique digits matching the winning numbers drawn, in any sequence, you win $208 (ex. 1234, 3142).
